#
# Custom recipe: SGLang v0.5.11 + our SM121 sgl-kernel patches.
#
# Pinned to upstream tag `v0.5.11` (commit 612785ffdcaf, 2026-05-05) — i.e.
# v0.5.10.post1 + 588 merged PRs including:
#   - Gemma 4 native support (#21952 + follow-ups #22079, #24048, #22842)
#   - Qwen3.6 + GLM-5.1 + MiMo-V2.5 + Kimi-K2.6 day-0 support
#   - Spec V2 default with overlap scheduling (#21062)
#   - DFLASH speculative decoding (#22077, #22358, #23553)
#   - Decode-side radix cache for PD disaggregation (#19746)
#   - FA3 community kernels (#20796) + fa3 scheduler-metadata precompute (#21104)
#   - is_layer_skipped() dot-boundary match — Qwen3.6-FP8 fix (#23467)
#   - EPLB Qwen3 fix (#21822)
#   - Streaming abort status_code fix (#22535)
#   - FlashInferCuteDslMoE layer (#21339) — additional fused-MoE backend
#   - Toolchain bump: PyTorch 2.9 → 2.11, CUDA 13.0 default, sgl-kernel 0.4.2,
#     flashinfer 0.6.7.post2 → 0.6.8.post1
#
# Delta from a hypothetical scitrera/dgx-spark-sglang:0.5.11 (not yet published
# by scitrera as of 2026-05-09): same SGLang ref, but with our six SM121
# sgl-kernel patches applied (see CUTLASS_NVFP4_SM121_PRD.md). Built from
# xomoxcc/dgx-spark-pytorch-dev:2.11.0-v1-cu132 instead of scitrera's
# (same recipe, our namespace).
#
# See SGLANG_v0.5.11_VERSION_CHANGES.md for the full delta vs v0.5.10.post1.
#
DOCKERFILE=Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
TARGET=runtime

# Upstream scitrera/cuda-containers sglang-0.5.10.recipe references
# scitrera/dgx-spark-pytorch-dev:2.11.0-v1-cu132, which scitrera committed
# a recipe for on 2026-04-08 but never built+published to Docker Hub (their
# main-dir recipes are built manually by the maintainer, no CI; the 2.11
# recipe originally pinned an unreleased NCCL fork from zyang-dev — we now
# build against upstream NVIDIA/nccl instead, see below).
#
# To avoid the ~45% perf regression of the 2.10 fallback (torch 2.10/cuda 13.1
# vs torch 2.11/cuda 13.2 in nvcc codegen + cuBLAS/cuDNN), we build the 2.11
# base image ourselves via scripts/build_pytorch_base_image.sh and tag it
# under our namespace. That build consumes the same recipe, now pinned to
# upstream NCCL v2.30.4-1 (NVIDIA/nccl). The former zyang-dev/nccl
# dgxspark-3node-ring fork patch turned out to be a default-off subnet-aware-
# routing feature — a verified no-op on our single-/24 switched (CRS812) fabric;
# see pytorch-2.12.0-dev-v1.recipe for the full analysis.
#
# Prerequisite: run scripts/build_pytorch_base_image.sh BEFORE
# build_sm121_image.sh on the build host. The result is kept in spark4's
# local podman store — not pushed to Docker Hub — so the sglang build
# finds it by name without a pull attempt.
BASE_IMAGE=xomoxcc/dgx-spark-pytorch-dev:2.11.0-v1-cu132

# flashinfer is bumped above v0.5.11's tested pin (0.6.8.post1) to **0.6.11**
# (released 2026-05-09) so that the `head_dim=512` fix (flashinfer PR #2959,
# in 0.6.10+) is included — this unblocks `attention_backend=flashinfer` for
# Gemma-4 global-attention layers (see FLASHINFER_HEAD_DIM_512_UPSTREAM_BUG.md).
# Risk: SGLang v0.5.11 was only tested against 0.6.8.post1 (release notes);
# 0.6.8 → 0.6.11 spans several non-trivial flashinfer changes (cute_dsl/moe
# refactors, FP8-MLA refactor, multiple SM120 bugfixes). If SGLang calls a
# flashinfer API that shifted in this window, expect runtime crashes — smoke
# the full model fleet (Qwen3-235B, GLM-4.7, Gemma-4 BF16+NVFP4) before
# promoting. Roll back to 0.6.8.post1 here if regressions surface.
FLASHINFER_VERSION=0.6.11
# transformers 5.8.0 is pinned (above v0.5.11's tested 5.7.x) so that the
# Gemma-4 *-assistant drafter checkpoints (released 2026-05-05, 4-layer
# auxiliary models for `google/gemma-4-{26B-A4B,31B}-it-assistant`) load
# correctly. Without this bump the drafter's config (Gemma-4 architecture
# subclass used for NEXTN/MTP speculative decoding) is unknown to the
# `transformers` `AutoConfig` registry and the SGLang head exits with
# `ValueError: Unrecognized configuration class ... gemma4_assistant`
# during drafter weight-loading. We need the drafter for MTP on Gemma-4
# (matrix tests 7–11 / 19–23 in the gemma-4-{31b-it,26b-a4b-it} sweeps).
TRANSFORMERS_VERSION=5.8.0

# Pinned to the v0.5.11 release tag (commit 612785ffdcaf, 2026-05-05).
# SGLANG_VERSION is set so setuptools-scm produces a clean "0.5.11" version
# string in the wheel; SGLANG_REF picks the corresponding git tag.
SGLANG_VERSION=0.5.11
SGLANG_REF="v0.5.11"

IMAGE_TAG=xomoxcc/dgx-spark-sglang:0.5.11-sm121
